[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating OAuth2 behavior**\n\nI'm considering how RestAssured.oauth2 works. It seems like there’s no need for a null check in static usage, but when calling authenticate, it might not handle null properly. A public API likely isn't designed to support null values, but executing a full request with null parameters could still return an 'ok' response.\n\nHowever, I need to check if handling null for authentication is documented. If not, using an access token directly could call the OAuth2Scheme, which might lead to a ClassCastException due to a known bug. Maybe using HTTPBuilder could help avoid this issue.\n\n**Assessing dynamic access in tests**\n\nI'm pondering whether the dynamic access will cover class$ in my tests. While it includes lines 29, 30, and 32, class$ seems to be excluded. I should look into improving test coverage for class methods.\n\nOh, and my tests might need to skip running if accessing the protected auth fails. The OAuth2Scheme.authenticate method from Groovy appears to access the protected field through metaclass. It seems this is just how the library operates with internal calls from RestAssured, which might affect RequestSpecificationImpl as well.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06c953a9b5c816d1016a26eb2439ac819590805ebb5d5bc2a6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJutAQb3f-UPh2nZbiR1j0BNHTv0yqoKYKn08xER0VdK54CayxZDhPjG9vo5my72QzyQx3ALhsTA4Bs6wmvzfqJH1-mx8paag6gMeEkV1cdkB7I2_RDksTEvnAB6aK0rPOEFR_OBfaCmUnWtUauBRnX5oCsBAayAKGRayNM_PhBAjoOH1ww3TlkN0LoIwFIOgv1Ng0t59EQLhS02t5uKmLSPCsJpblL-zZHvn-EUx11bLSi_ww3qJPII3YFG1yEwMAAin7bM3PffFar8edXzsbaxQvFMeUMdR_Ugjpm8O5vJfly_Ap2oVUIdp-Cv1xy4QqpIuvITvoTVAxyKbZ9Ctv26dQVdGMeFavQIAqG4gYgIcAi0dhqigyf1c4YYrk0tn3GuPUgxVV4u-wK-lLzgKFCnfh8f7YH0FRxibaquhXPX0gH6LaZ-9G1ZPkjVIZyCt20TKfdslOlZtpg-KOuKzyTmJN2f7UKD4yd0fLZem_i_9gY5jNDC9o6N-UzhKWLn4bq0aV37NMoyjTHKpj8mUTbDq6Kz